Installation of jrat software is performed by calling specified target within
ant script. Typicall installation procedure is realized by issuing the following
command:

$ ant install

In this case the software will be installed with 64-bit Unix libraries in 
the default directory /opt.
For other operating systems use one of the following parameter:

* 32-bit Unix
$ ant -Dversion=32 install

* 32-bit Windows
$ ant -Dversion=win32 install

* 64-bit Windows
$ ant -Dversion=win64 install 
 
In order to override installation in default directory, you can provide 
a paramater for the ant installation script:

$ ant -Dprefix=/my/install/dir install

The prefix denotes target installation directory.

Dependencies: jrat requires some libraries from the HDF Java Object Package.
The set of files includes the following shared libraries: 

- libjhdf.so
- libjhdf5.so

Installation script will create a bash script called jrat.
It will be placed in /usr/bin directory for easy access.
After installetion you can run jrat by typing in a terminal:

$ jrat

To receive help type:

$ jrat -h

Documentation of jrat software is performed by calling specified target within
ant script:

$ ant doc



 
